3.3 Empires: Belief Systems
...

Essential Question

How did different belief systems endure or change during the period from 1450-1750?

Roman Catholic Church > 1500

The Catholic Church claimed to be the continuation of Peter, the old Pope. And people believe that the pope is a direct descendent of Jesus.

Cracks

Cracks begin to appear in the Church's sayings. The Church lies to the public, and they affirm that Latin is the Lord's language. As you translate the Bible, mistakes happen because words do not translate one to one.

France is Catholic, Portugal is Catholic, Spain is Catholic, so the power really is in Rome.

Corruption

Indulgences.

The waters were perfect for a revolution. Which is why came the Protestant revolution.

Protestant Reformation
...

Church of England

Russia

Russia was watching the tensions mount between Charles V and the Holy Roman Empire, and had the decision to replace the Patriarch of the Russian Orthodox Church with a Synod. In general, Russia had very little to do with the Protestant Reformation, as its church was already established as the Eastern Orthodox Church.

Wars of Religion
...

1555 Peace of Augsburg- Allowed German states to choose Catholic or Lutheran

Catholic and Huguenots fought for half a century in France

  • King Henry IV, who was raised Protestant became Catholic to unify the country
  • Edict of Nantes, allowed religious toleration
  • 1685, Louis XIV of France, issued a Revocation of the Edict of Nantes, heavily affecting the economy

Thirty Years War

  • 1618-1648
  • Led mostly to economic catastrophe

Peace of Westphalia

  • The Holy Roman allowed each to select a religion
    • France, Spain, Italy choose Catholic
    • Northern Europe was either Lutheran or Calvinist
    • England was Protestant with a state church (Church of England)

3.4 Comparison in Land-Based Empires
...

Historical Evidence
...

When you want to include Historical Evidence (Outside Evidence) you need to make sure it does not overlap with document evidence in (DBQ).

Historical evidence needs to be specific, so things such as Historical figures, Events, Empires, Technology, etc.

You cannot be too broad, so things such as saying an empire was very involved in trade is NOT specific enough and thus does not work as Historical Evidence.

Make sure you link the evidence you use to the argument. It MUST support the argument.

...

Evidence:

The Evidence on the right is not specific. Thus, it does not work.
